FBIS3-1903 "drchi042_d_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-042 Document Type:Daily Report 3 Mar 1994 Northeast Asia More on Visit OW0303012494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0041 GMT 3 Mar 94 OW0303012494 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Kitakyushu, Japan, March 2 (XINHUA) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji today visited Yasukawa Electrical Corp., a leading Japanese robot manufacturer located in this industrial city in southwestern Japan. Zhu inspected a computerized robot production and research facility called Motorman Center, where he saw robots arranging flowers, assembling robots and writing. The Chinese vice-premier said he hoped that Yasukawa would expand its cooperation with China, including technology transfer. Zhu is here on his last leg of a nine-day Japan trip. Earlier, he visited Toto Ltd., a major sanitary wear maker in Japan.
